    <fluff>
        <overview>Compared to Johnston Industries’ radical Hatchetman HCT-7D and the Republic’s experimental HCT-7R, Defiance’s HCT-8S takes a more measured approach by combining—and improving upon—features of the -6S and -7S models. While the ’Mech’s primary firepower is still supplied by a trusty Defiance Disintegrator LB 10-X autocannon, it is now backed-up by a pair of Clan-grade ER medium lasers. Its speed is enhanced by a ClanTech engine as used on most of Defiance’s current products, also improving survivability. Double-strength heat sinks round out the package, allowing the -8S to operate without fear of heat build-up.</overview>
        <capabilities></capabilities>
