        <variants></variants>
        <notables>First Leutnant Cory Inglis: A new member of the Fifth Lyran Regulars in 3144, the then-sergeant’s trial by fire came the following year in the form of a determined assault by elements of the Jade Falcon’s Gamma Galaxy. Assigned to the factory world of Loxley along with six of the Regulars’ twelve companies, the week-long battle saw four of those companies destroyed. In the midst of the action, his heavily damaged unit was twice combined with other battered companies, and Inglis was breveted to leutnant as casualties mounted.:br::br::tab:Fighting a guerilla defense amongst the Gray Mountains, he personally claimed three OmniMech kills in as many days, all of which were heavier units. His actions went a long way to safeguard Loxley’s vital factories and earned him a full commission to first leutnant, while the Fifth Regulars as a whole were awarded the Falconslayers Medallion for their efforts. Playing an active role in rebuilding the unit, intelligence reports suggest Inglis may soon be promoted to hauptmann.</notables>
